<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871014-0014 </DOCNO><HL> Xerox Corp. FormsVoice-Systems Unit</HL><DD> 10/14/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> XRX </IN><DATELINE> STAMFORD, Conn.  </DATELINE><TEXT>    Xerox Corp. said it formed avoice-systems division to market voice-related products andintegrate them with other Xerox office products.   The new division, a unit of the Xerox Special Markets group, will market voice-related products that enable users to send spoken messages into the computer memory banks of fellow users. The division also will market software that will keep track of system usage and bill users automatically. Xerox makes copiers and electronic printing systems.    Bernard Kinsey, formerly vice president and executive assistant to the president of the Custom Systems division, was named vice president and general manager of the voice-systems division.    Xerox closed in composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange yesterday at $75.75 a share, up 75 cents. </TEXT></DOC>